        "sender_full_name": "Robin Arnez",
        "timestamp": 1771941276
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Huh, indeed, the <code>grind</code> proof do use this instance, and if I were to re-define my own Unit type, then I would need to apply the same kind of workaround.</p>\n<p>I thought that <code>grind</code> could see through my definition of <code>compare</code>, but actually proved <code>ReflOrd</code> using some kind of defeq abuse and then proved the other properties (e.g. <code>OrientedOrd</code> or <code>TransOrd</code>) without ever needing the definition of <code>compare</code>.</p>\n<p>Nevermind then, thanks for the insights!</p>",
